# GitHub Issue Templates

Create these files in `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/` folder:

## 1. Bug Report Template
**File: `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/bug_report.md`**

```markdown
---
name: Bug report
about: Create a report to help us improve
title: '[BUG] '
labels: bug
assignees: ''
---

## Bug Description
A clear and concise description of what the bug is.

## Steps to Reproduce
1. Go to '...'
2. Click on '....'
3. Scroll down to '....'
4. See error

## Expected Behavior
A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen.

## Actual Behavior
A clear and concise description of what actually happened.

## Screenshots
If applicable, add screenshots to help explain your problem.

## Environment
- OS: [e.g. macOS, Windows, Linux]
- Browser: [e.g. Chrome, Firefox, Safari]
- Node.js version: [e.g. 18.17.0]
- Project version: [e.g. 1.0.0]

## Integration Details
- [ ] HubSpot integration affected
- [ ] Grain integration affected
- [ ] JIRA integration affected
- [ ] Slack integration affected
- [ ] Database/Supabase affected
- [ ] Webhook endpoints affected

## Error Logs
```
Paste any error logs here
```

## Additional Context
Add any other context about the problem here.

## Possible Solution
If you have ideas on how to fix this, please describe them here.
```

## 2. Feature Request Template
**File: `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/feature_request.md`**

```markdown
---
name: Feature request
about: Suggest an idea for this project
title: '[FEATURE] '
labels: enhancement
assignees: ''
---

## Feature Description
A clear and concise description of what you want to happen.

## Problem/Use Case
Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.
A clear and concise description of what the problem is. Ex. I'm always frustrated when [...]

## Proposed Solution
A clear and concise description of what you want to happen.

## Alternative Solutions
A clear and concise description of any alternative solutions or features you've considered.

## Initiative Alignment
Which strategic initiative does this feature align with?
- [ ] Customer Research System
- [ ] Competitive Intelligence Agent
- [ ] Marketing Content Pipeline
- [ ] Automated Product Updates
- [ ] Other (please specify)

## Impact Assessment
- **Priority**: High / Medium / Low
- **Effort**: High / Medium / Low
- **Value**: High / Medium / Low

## Integration Requirements
Which integrations would this feature affect?
- [ ] HubSpot API
- [ ] Grain API
- [ ] JIRA API
- [ ] Slack API
- [ ] Supabase database
- [ ] AI/ML providers (OpenAI/Claude)
- [ ] Webhook endpoints

## Acceptance Criteria
What would need to be true for this feature to be considered complete?
- [ ] Criteria 1
- [ ] Criteria 2
- [ ] Criteria 3

## Additional Context
Add any other context, mockups, or examples about the feature request here.
```

## 3. Task/Enhancement Template
**File: `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/task.md`**

```markdown
---
name: Task/Enhancement
about: Create a task or enhancement for project development
title: '[TASK] '
labels: task
assignees: ''
---

## Task Description
A clear and concise description of what needs to be done.

## Related Initiative
Which initiative does this task belong to?
- [ ] Initiative 1: Customer Research System
- [ ] Initiative 2: Competitive Intelligence Agent
- [ ] Initiative 3: Marketing Content Pipeline
- [ ] Initiative 4: Automated Product Updates

## Task Details
- **Task ID**: T### (if applicable)
- **Priority**: High / Medium / Low
- **Estimated Effort**: # hours/days
- **Phase**: Foundation / Data Integration / AI Analysis / User Interface / Product Updates

## Requirements
What are the specific requirements for this task?
- [ ] Requirement 1
- [ ] Requirement 2
- [ ] Requirement 3

## Technical Specifications
- **Technologies involved**: [e.g. Next.js, Supabase, HubSpot API]
- **Database changes**: Yes / No
- **API endpoints**: Yes / No
- **UI components**: Yes / No

## Definition of Done
What criteria must be met for this task to be considered complete?
- [ ] Code implemented and tested
- [ ] Documentation updated
- [ ] Tests passing
- [ ] Code reviewed
- [ ] Deployed to staging/production

## Dependencies
Are there any dependencies or blockers?
- [ ] Dependency 1
- [ ] Dependency 2

## Notes
Any additional notes or considerations for this task.
```

## 4. Documentation Template
**File: `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/documentation.md`**

```markdown
---
name: Documentation
about: Request documentation improvements or additions
title: '[DOCS] '
labels: documentation
assignees: ''
---

## Documentation Request
What documentation needs to be created or improved?

## Type of Documentation
- [ ] API documentation
- [ ] User guide
- [ ] Developer guide
- [ ] Integration guide
- [ ] Troubleshooting guide
- [ ] Code comments
- [ ] README updates
- [ ] Other (please specify)

## Target Audience
Who is the primary audience for this documentation?
- [ ] End users
- [ ] Developers
- [ ] System administrators
- [ ] Contributors
- [ ] Other (please specify)

## Current State
Describe the current state of the documentation (if any).

## Proposed Changes
What specific changes or additions are needed?

## Success Criteria
How will we know when this documentation is complete and useful?
- [ ] Criteria 1
- [ ] Criteria 2
- [ ] Criteria 3

## Additional Context
Any additional context, examples, or references that would be helpful.
```

## 5. Integration Issue Template
**File: `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/integration.md`**

```markdown
---
name: Integration Issue
about: Report issues with third-party integrations
title: '[INTEGRATION] '
labels: integration
assignees: ''
---

## Integration Affected
Which integration is experiencing issues?
- [ ] HubSpot CRM
- [ ] Grain Meetings
- [ ] JIRA Project Management
- [ ] Slack Notifications
- [ ] Supabase Database
- [ ] AI Providers (OpenAI/Claude)
- [ ] Zapier Webhooks
- [ ] Other (please specify)

## Issue Description
A clear and concise description of the integration issue.

## Error Details
```
Paste any error messages, logs, or status codes here
```

## Integration Configuration
- **API Version**: [e.g. HubSpot API v3]
- **Authentication Method**: [e.g. Private App, OAuth]
- **Endpoint**: [e.g. /crm/v3/objects/contacts]
- **Rate Limits**: [if applicable]

## Steps to Reproduce
1. Step 1
2. Step 2
3. Step 3
4. See error

## Expected Behavior
What should happen with this integration?

## Actual Behavior
What is actually happening?

## Environment
- **Environment**: Development / Staging / Production
- **Last Working**: [date/time when it last worked]
- **Recent Changes**: [any recent changes that might be related]

## Impact Assessment
- **Severity**: Critical / High / Medium / Low
- **Affected Users**: [number or percentage]
- **Business Impact**: [description of business impact]

## Troubleshooting Attempted
What troubleshooting steps have you already tried?
- [ ] Checked API credentials
- [ ] Verified API endpoint URLs
- [ ] Checked rate limits
- [ ] Reviewed error logs
- [ ] Tested with different data
- [ ] Other (please specify)

## Additional Context
Any additional context about the integration issue.
```

## Usage Instructions

1. **Create the directory structure**:
   ```bash
   mkdir -p .github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE
   ```

2. **Create each template file** with the content above

3. **Customize the templates** for your specific needs

4. **Test the templates** by creating a new issue in your repository

These templates will help standardize issue reporting and make it easier to track and resolve problems across your AI Customer Intelligence Platform project!
